I made a design for a thing called "Digital Literacy for Students". This design has three parts: things that are good to know about digital tools, how to be safe on the internet and how to look good online. There is also a part about being nice in emails.

I used colors and pictures for each part so people can see what it is about and understand it easily. For example the part about tools has pictures of apps you can use to take notes store things in the cloud and be more productive. The part about being safe on the internet talks about having passwords keeping things private and being careful about fake emails.

The part, about looking online shows how to have a clean profile use a good photo and make friends in a good way. The email part reminds people to be nice, clear and polite when they send emails.

One thing that was hard to do was make it easy to understand and also look good. It was not easy to take ideas and make them short and simple and then find pictures that fit with them.. I learned that using pictures and simple words can really help people learn about digital things and be good online
